    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Validation results demonstrate CFD predictions of NIH within 12% of experimental measurements across the COU operating envelope. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. The model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Note: aleatory uncertainty from inter-donor red blood cell fragility variability at nominal flow conditions was characterized qualitatively in the validation narrative but was not linked to a structured uncertainty quantification record; this limitation is acknowledged and accepted at MRL 2 given the conservative acceptance threshold applied.",
